b'' b'' b'a new alternative to scouting for those "unacceptable to bsa" for reasons' b'of religious or sexual preference:' b'' b'' b'' b'"birth announcement" on march from earth forum, compuserve' b'information service' b'===================================================================' b'' b'formal announcement' b'-------------------' b'' b'(sm)' b'enviroleague' b'' b'a new youth movement,"enviroleague," was recently born, according to its' b'founder, boyd r. critz, iii (cis id# of peoria, illinois.' b'enviroleague exists for the education of youth, both male and female, in' b'matters concerning their values related to and responsibility for our' b'environment.' b'' b'incorporated as an illinois not-for-profit corporation, its articles and' b'initial applications for a service mark have now been filed. according to' b'critz, its draft bylaws contain the following statement of mission and' b'objectives:' b'' b'mission' b'' b'it is the mission of enviroleague and its adult members' b'to foster and implement the improved education of young' b'people in the need to conduct their lives as stewards' b'of the earth, to leave the earth in a better condition' b'than they found it, and to otherwise act as responsible,' b'moral and ethical users of their environment. to pursue' b'the accomplishment of this mission, enviroleague shall' b'seek to serve as a catalyst, focusing in common cause the' b'separate efforts of all groups desiring the preservation,' b'improvement, and responsible use of the environment in' b'which we must all live.' b'' b'objectives' b'' b'in pursuit of the mission of enviroleague, its primary' b'objectives shall be:' b'(1) to establish a movement involving as many' b'environmentally concerned organizations as' b'possible, said movement having as its primary' b'focus the education and participatory' b'involvement of young people in appropriate areas' b'of environmental concern;' b'(2) to develop and provide to such organizations and' b'their branches a full complement of program' b'materials for their use, including suitable' b'uniforms, insignia and other badges, written' b'ideas, syllabi and information, literature and' b'other items as shall seem appropriate and' b'desirable;' b'(3) to serve as a "clearing house" for the exchange' b'of program ideas, materials and information' b'among said organizations; and' b'(4) to assist environmentally concerned' b'organizations to recruit and train the necessary' b'adult leadership for their youth programs.' b'' b'enviroleague will operate through three "program divisions" serving youth in' b'the elementary, middle and high school grades, respectively. service shall be' b'through formation of "enviroleague teams," either by enviroleague itself or by' b'environmentally conscious organizations (or their local branches) wishing a' b'charter to use programs developed by enviroleague.' b'' b'enviroleague, as it develops, will be controlled by the actual adult leaders' b'of each local team, and will have no nationally imposed obstacles to' b'membership or adult leadership status not based upon relevant improper' b'conduct. organizations accepting a charter may, however, impose certain' b'additional standards for their own use of the program material. should such' b'organizations do so, enviroleague will commit itself to forming, as soon as' b'possible, new nearby teams having no such restrictions, particularly as to' b'youth membership.' b'' b'enviroleague will operate on the principle that youth will have much to' b'contribute to developing its programs. thus, the top youth leaders of its' b'teams for middle and high school youth may become involved in governing any' b'local administrative groups, and those for its high school youth may be' b'involved in similar functions at the national level.' b'' b'program materials are in development at this time. copies of the "draft"' b"portions of the mentor's manual (manual for adult leadership) will be in the" b'earth forum, library these files will be updated as development takes' b'place.' b'' b"compuserve is particularly proud that enviroleague's founder chose this" b'electronic medium to make the first public announcement of its formation.' b'this announcement is being made simultaneously in both the outdoor and earth' b'forums.' b'' b"the electronic home of enviroleague is in compuserve's earth forum go" b'earth message and library areas both named "enviroleague."' b'============================================================================' b'' b"subsequently, enviroleague's initial governance council has held its first" b'meeting. boyd critz was elected as the first enviroleague chief guardian' b'(equivalent to chairman of the board or ceo). he can be reached at home' b'(309) in case of real need. also, mail can be addressed to:' b'enviroleague' b'p.o. box b'peoria, il b'' b'those interested in starting an enviroleague team might just establish' b'contact, to receive a diskette (ibm dos, ascii) with initial information.' b'--' b'' b'' 